rs Zayas's intention to reform the Spanish nobility by displaying noble misbehaviour and its deadly consequences. Her book concludes by detailing the Desengaños' intriguing influence on the aesthetic base of Gothic literature by revealing that its authors were avid readers of Zayas.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aDeath in literature. 0aMeaning (Philosophy) in literature. 0aWomen in literature. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144269624240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442696242423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442696242.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK